.TH "ftrace_location" 9 "ftrace_location" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ftrace_location \- return true if the ip giving is a traced location
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "unsigned long" ftrace_location
.BI "(unsigned long ip "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ip" 12
the instruction pointer to check
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns rec->ip if \fIip\fP given is a pointer to a ftrace location.
That is, the instruction that is either a NOP or call to
the function tracer. It checks the ftrace internal tables to
determine if the address belongs or not.
